cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.DS, cs.PF, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with load-balancing techniques for parallelization of graph applications on GPUs. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on GPU acceleration of graph applications. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses Breadth First Search and Single Source Shortest Paths as processing kernels. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper aims to improve load-balancing for better performance of graph applications on GPUs. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still relevant as the paper may discuss programming models or languages used for GPU programming.
